Lenovo, Rio, STX, Malaysia Marine: Asia Ex-Japan Equity Preview

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-05-08T21:43:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/lenovo-rio-stx-malaysia-marine-asia-ex-japan-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Asian trading, excluding  Japan .
Stock symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close, unless noted otherwise.  Lenovo Group Ltd. (992)  (992 HK): Lenovo’s video game venture
will begin sales of a game-console product this year, Jack Luo,
head of the venture, said in Beijing. Lenovo,  China ’s biggest
maker of personal computers, set up Beijing Eedoo Technology Ltd.
last year to enter the game console market. Lenovo rose 0.5
percent to HK$4.33.  Malaysia Marine & Heavy Engineering Holdings Bhd. (MMHE MK):
The Malaysian rig-building arm of MISC Bhd. (MISC MK) said net
income in the fourth quarter, ended March 31, rose 12 percent
from a year earlier to 128.6 million ringgit, according to a
company statement. The stock fell 0.2 percent to 6.83 ringgit.  Rio Tinto  Group (RIO AU): The world’s second-largest mining
company extended its takeover offer for  Riversdale Mining Ltd. (RIV) 
by two weeks to May 20, unless further extended. Rio Tinto now
holds a relevant interest in about 73.28 percent of Riversdale
shares. Rio dropped 1.9 percent to A$79.57. Riversdale (RIV AU)
added 0.5 percent to A$16.58.  STX Corp. (011810 KS): The holding company for  South
Korea ’s STX Group plans to raise 205 billion won ($189 million)
by selling 10 million new shares. The funds will be used for
resource development and overseas businesses, according to a
regulatory filing. STX Corp. slid 5.3 percent to 25,200 won.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
